<item>
            <title>[LU-19507] nodemap RBAC role for setting inode attributes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19507</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to have a nodemap RBAC role to control whether the root user on a client can set clear the IMMUTABLE and APPEND_ONLY (and potentially other) inode attribute flags on files and directories.  This would allow one mountpoint with the appropriate RBAC to create files that are marked immutable/append, and another mountpoint to be unable to remove the immutable/append flags from the files even as root.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This might be an alternative or complementary to the &quot;immutable inherit&quot; flag in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18679&quot; title=&quot;Allow setting an &amp;quot;immutable inherit&amp;quot; flag on a directory&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18679&quot;&gt;LU-18679&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
